RACE.FOOTNOTES: A KISS FOR KHOZAN set the pace inside, was confidently handled rounding the turn, cued approaching the quarter and opened up into the lane, drifted out passing the sixteenth pole, but was clear. FOREVER UNCAPTURED got rank as the gate opened and bumped with an outer foe, stalked in the two path, tipped out early around the turn and ranged up from the four path passing the quarter, was cued from the three path into the stretch, and chased on for place. GLAZED GINGER bumped with an inner foe then an outer foe at the start, prompted the pace in the three path, attempted to bid under coaxing early around the turn, flattened while floating out to the five path in upper stretch, but held show. MO RISSA broke in and brushed with an inner foe at the start, raced off the pace in the two path and made no impact. HIDDEN ROAD chased in the four path but did not threaten. FAR ABOVE always trailed around the three path.
